  "text": "Seven common haplotypes (designated M1-M7) account for 99% of MHC class I and II diversity in Mauritian derived Cynomolgus macaques [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This restricted MHC diversity of Mauritian-derived cynomolgus macaques makes it possible to relate CMI responses to haplotype [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . MHC haplotypes of macaques were determined by microsatellite PCR as described previously [CITATION_5] . Where recombination was observed allele-specific, PCR was employed to resolve individual alleles carried by each animal.",
